# Multi-Feature Improvements

## Overview
Addresses 7 distinct bugs and feature requests across appointments, patient records, profiles, and doctor availability.

---

## 1. Appointment Phone Duplicate Logic (Bug Fix)

**Problem:** [findExistingAppointment](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#208-224) queries for ANY scheduled appointment across ALL dates, so it incorrectly warns when a second appointment on a DIFFERENT date is created. When cancelled, the first appointment stays. After 2 slots — 3rd still gets accepted.

**Fix:**
- [findExistingAppointment](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#208-224) should only check appointments **on the same date** as the new booking (not globally).  
- Change the check: if an existing scheduled appointment is found **for the same date**, warn and offer to reschedule.  
- For different dates: allow freely — no warning.

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)
- Remove global check; keep the date filter mandatory so duplicate prevention is scoped per-date only.

#### [MODIFY] [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)
- Pass the selected date to [findExistingAppointment](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#208-224) call.

---

## 2. Phone Call Button (Bug Fix)

**Problem:** Phone icon in [_ScheduleCard](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#643-678) is not functional.

**Fix:**
- Add `url_launcher` package.
- Wrap the phone icon `GestureDetector` with `launchUrl(Uri(scheme: 'tel', path: phone))`.

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)
- Find phone icon button and wire up `url_launcher`.

#### [MODIFY] [pubspec.yaml](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/pubspec.yaml)
- Add `url_launcher: ^6.3.0`.

---

## 3. Patient Address — Split into City + Area (Enhancement)

**Problem:** Address is a single text field combining city and area.

**Decision:** Since PocketBase schema change is needed, we'll store as two separate app-level fields and serialize them into one field as `"area, city"` or add two new PB fields. Given no schema migration tool, we'll split in the UI and store as two PocketBase fields.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This requires **adding two new fields** (`city`, `area`) to the `patients` PocketBase collection. The user must do this manually in PocketBase admin UI: add `city` (Text) and `area` (Text) fields to the `patients` collection.

#### [MODIFY] [patient_model.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/models/patient_model.dart)
- Add `city` and `area` fields alongside existing `address`.

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)
- Add `city` and `area` to [createPatient](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#130-168).

#### [MODIFY] [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)
- Split address field into City and Area text fields.

#### [MODIFY] [patient_info_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart)
- Show city and area separately.

#### [MODIFY] [patient_profile_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_profile_screen.dart)
- Display city and area in patient profile.

