## 6. Availability — Generic Default + Multiple Breaks (Enhancement)

**Problems:**
1. Schedule is configured per-day individually. User wants to set a default schedule once and apply to all days, then deselect non-working days.
2. Breaktime is accepted outside of working hours — must validate break times are within start/end.
3. Only 1 break time slot per day — needs support for multiple breaks.

#### [MODIFY] [edit_doctor_details_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/settings/screens/edit_doctor_details_screen.dart)
- **Default schedule:** Add "Apply to All Working Days" template section at top of Availability tab with start time, end time, and breaks. Clicking "Apply to All" propagates values to all selected days.
- **Break validation:** In [_save()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/settings/screens/edit_doctor_details_screen.dart#207-325), validate that break start/end are within working hours; show error if outside.
- **Multiple breaks:** Change break structure from `breakStart`/`breakEnd` (single) to `List<{start, end}>` per day. Update [WorkingSchedule](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/auth/models/doctor_model.dart#4-39) model and UI to support adding/removing multiple breaks.

#### [MODIFY] [doctor_model.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/auth/models/doctor_model.dart)
- Update [WorkingSchedule](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/auth/models/doctor_model.dart#4-39) to hold `List<Map<String,String>> breaks` instead of single `breakStart`/`breakEnd`.

#### [MODIFY] [scheduling_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/scheduling_service.dart)
- Update slot generation to skip ALL break windows, not just one.

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Create two appointments for the same phone on different dates → no warning shown.
2. Create two appointments for the same phone on the same date → warning shown, cancel keeps original.
3. Tap phone icon on an appointment card → phone app opens with number pre-filled.
4. Create a patient with separate City and Area fields → saved and displayed separately.
5. Clinic profile shows logo, address, phone, location fields.
6. Doctor profile shows photo, phone, DOB fields.
7. Set a default schedule and "Apply to All" → all selected days inherit times.
8. Set a break outside working hours → save shows validation error.
9. Add 2 breaks per day → both respected in slot generation.
